  "title": "Project-command approval gate and command execution",
  "summary": "Worktrunk runs arbitrary project-defined hook commands, alias steps, and --execute bodies. These must only run after the approval gate (`Approvals` + `approve_command_batch` / `approve_or_skip`) clears them. Bypassing the gate = remote code execution on `wt switch`. Also handles signal-derived child exits (Ctrl-C must abort, not get swallowed by `FailureStrategy::Warn`). See CLAUDE.md > Project Commands Run Only After Approval and Signal Handling.",
